==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tricrotism
<hw>Tri"cro*tism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>That condition of the arterial pulse in which there is a triple
beat. The pulse curve obtained in the sphygmographic tracing
characteristic of tricrotism shows two secondary crests in addition to
the primary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1538 -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tricrotous</ent>⟦br⟧
